                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bæzn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bæzn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bæzdæ</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>толщина</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>thickness</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>густота</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>density</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Отвлеченное от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæz-"/> ‘толстый’, образованное суффиксом -%in%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>-na</w></mentioned>), как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærn"/> ‘ответственность’ от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>hvarnah-</w></mentioned> (ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_farn"/>) от <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>hvar-</w></mentioned> и т. п. В <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>bæzdæ</w></mentioned> %id%i возникло, вероятно, перебойно из %in%i (*%ibæznæ%i → %ibæzdæ%i), ср. аналогичный перебой в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæznyg"/> || qæzdyg ‘богатый’, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>ǧæzdæ</w> <gloss><q>богатство</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>32, 33, 37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>596</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">An abstract word derived from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæz-"/> ‘thick’ with the suffix -%in%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>-na</w></mentioned>), like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærn"/> ‘responsibility’ from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bar"/>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>hvarnah-</w></mentioned> (Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_farn"/>) from <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>hvar-</w></mentioned> and so on. In <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>bæzdæ</w></mentioned> %id%i appeared probably from the transition of %in%i (*%ibæznæ%i → %ibæzdæ%i), cf. an similar transition in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæznyg"/> || %iqæzdyg%i ‘rich’, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>ǧæzdæ</w> <gloss><q>wealth</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>32, 33, 37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>596</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>